			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A bit of help/adding.  Main is an SK, I deal with rampage / enrage / flurry quite often.
<br />

<br />
Flurry:  With the MOB you're attacking gets off extra attacks (between 1 and 5) in a given melee round.  It will say: <span style="text-decoration: underline">mob_02 executes a flurry of attacks on warrior_01</span>
<br />

<br />
Enrage:  When you're within the front 90% of a mob (basically 45% either direction of the MT) you'll be hit with what's called "enrage" Enrage is a term that means all attacks get reposted.  Lets say you're in HoT (down in ToV) and you are attacking a wurm, when the wurm hits 10% or so, it will say <span style="text-decoration: underline">Wurm_002 Enrages </span>and everyone from the front 90% (which *should* only be the mt/sa really) will stop attacking, while everyone else should be behind the mob _the other 270%_ so they won't get their attacks reposted against them.
<br />

<br />
Rampage:  Rampage occurs when the MOB gets an extra set of attacks towards another person (does NOT have to be within melee range) It say <span style="text-decoration: underline">Mob_003 rampages</span> *note: it will not say it's target*  This target is assigned (post may 2003 patch) almost randomly now, in PoStorms Lords, Vindi, RumbleCrush we could not get and set a designated Rampage Target.  (Notice 1 from PoP, Luclin, Velious)  It now seems *seems* that rampage will hit whomever has done the most hate since the last rampage.   I can not confirm this, but due to engaging quite a few mobs, this is how it <span style="font-style: italic">seems</span>.   I hope this helps, JT feel free to delete/edit any old or unuseful information.<br />_________________<br />Melcore~</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
