			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd just like to add a few things to help clear it up <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Rampage range is the range of the mobs attack range.. So against mobs with huge attack range (such as ssra snakes) its extremely difficult to get out of range and still attack.. However against mobs with small attack ranges (Vindicator) all you need to do is step back..
<br />

<br />
But beware, doing this will place another friend on the list if they are closer <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> and this does not remove you from the list
<br />

<br />
So if you're 1st on the rampage list and step away then 2nd will get it.. If you move back into range then you're back on the list
<br />

<br />
Rampage doesnt seem to be affected by aggro either, it generally stays with the same person the entire fight
<br />

<br />
Atleast in some luclin encounters rampage also is not erased by dying.. There has been numerous times when a rezzed person would instantly be back on the rampage list and killed again.. 
<br />

<br />
AE rampage works the same way, its based on the attack range of the mob but hits everyone on the aggro list
<br />

<br />
Also, if your pet gets on the rampage list each subsequent pet will ALSO be on it.. Its a very useful tactic for absorbing damage.. If you got Host of the elements use it and watch them each take a round.. THey may only have 100 hp but they'll take a full 3000 pt hit <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/YlaineEQ/cheersig2.jpg" />
<br />
