			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd like to add my few words to this guide.  First off, great job on this.
<br />

<br />
From my experiences over the years, this is what I can recall:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Rampage:</span>
<br />

<br />
1. <span style="text-decoration: underline">Why did Rampage come about?</span>
<br />
During the Velious Era, and to some degree the endgame of Kunark, PC's had developed a single, almost all-encompassing strategy, which given certain constraints, could overcome any mob in the game.  Single-Tank Aggro, with a Complete Healing Chain.
<br />

<br />
In essence, PC's basically said, <span style="font-style: italic">"This tank is going to be the choke point.  In order for the NPC to kill all of us, he has to get through this tank.  We now put all of our resources into keeping this tank alive."</span>
<br />

<br />
With the exception of needing healing from AEs / breath weapons, only one person was going to be taking damage.  If that person never died, neither would anyone else.
<br />

<br />
Rampage was invented so warrior-class mobs could, in essence, damage two PC's at once without the need to add an AE Spell to them.  This meant other people could die, even if the Main Tank was still alive, and somewhat limiting the effectiveness of simply keeping a single Tank Alive.
<br />

<br />
2. <span style="text-decoration: underline">What does Rampage do?</span>
<br />
Each attack round, any NPC with rampage could execute a rampage attack.  There were two theories during the Velious Era, which i don't recall if one or the other were ever disproved.  Rampage Attacks break down like this:
<br />
<ul><li>Velious Era Theory 1 - the Rampage target took <span style="font-weight: bold">two mainhand attacks</span> from the NPC.
<br />
<li>Velious Era Theory 2 - the <span style="font-weight: bold">top six people on the aggro list took one mainhand attack each</span> from the NPC.
<br />
<li>Luclin Era - the Rampage target took <span style="font-weight: bold">two mainhand attacks</span> from the NPC.
<br />
<li>Planes of Power Era - certain NPC's can <span style="font-weight: bold">Area Effect</span> rampage.  Fennin Ro, the Tyrant of Fire is one such mob.  Each time the NPC executes a Rampage Attack, <span style="font-weight: bold">anyone within the NPC's melee range takes two mainhand attacks</span> from the NPC.  It is important to note, <span style="font-weight: bold">this includes the NPC's current target</span>.</ul>
<br />
3. <span style="text-decoration: underline">What is Flurry?</span>
<br />
Flurry only applies to the NPC's current target.  Each time a Flurry attack is executed, the NPC's current target receives <span style="font-weight: bold">two extra mainhand attacks</span> from the NPC in addition to those in the attack round.  An NPC which normally quads can now hit for as much as six attacks per round.<br />_________________<br /><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=539546>Strax Glittereye - 65 Magician</a>
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=539570>Wyndam Kindheart - 65 Cleric</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
